The article discusses the recent decrease in annual inflation to its lowest level since March 2021 and the zero monthly inflation rate. This, along with the news of the economy growing by over 5% in the last quarter, provides some relief for families during the holiday season. The efforts to mend supply chains and reduce inflation have been successful, but there is still work to be done as prices remain high for many families. The focus is on calling on corporations to lower costs for the middle class, while Republicans in Congress prioritize lowering taxes for the wealthy and large corporations.